The paper deals with the construction of a large-scale image dataset using deep learning with humans in the loop. This involves using deep learning algorithms to automate the labeling process and then involving humans to refine the labels. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning algorithms to optimize the performance of visual recognition models, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of classification confidence to split the dataset into positives, negatives, and unlabeled, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of convolutional networks to train on the dataset, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
